    <p class="flavor">
      These tools run entirely in your browser &mdash; no server, no login,
      no internet required after the page loads. Open them on a laptop or
      tablet at the table and they&rsquo;re ready to go.
    </p>

    <!-- ── Zone Tracker ──────────────────────────────── -->

    <h2 id="zone-tracker">Zone Tracker</h2>

    <p>
      Track Aetheric and Galvanic accumulation in real time. Set your area&rsquo;s
      baseline, click buttons as spells are cast and exotic weapons fire, and
      the tracker automatically calculates the current Reliability and Casting
      Target modifiers &mdash; no mental math required.
    </p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Feature</th><th>What It Does</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Baseline control</td><td>Set the area&rsquo;s permanent zone level (&minus;30 to +30)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Spell buttons</td><td>One click per spell tier (Weak +1 through Spectacular +4)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Weapon buttons</td><td>One click per Galvanic weapon shot (Rating 1 through 3)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Live effects</td><td>Shows Reliability and Casting modifiers, plus example weapon and caster</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Decay controls</td><td>Simulate 1, 5, or 10 minutes of decay (1 point per minute)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Activity log</td><td>Color-coded history of every shift and decay</td></tr>
    </table>

    <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
      <a href="tools/zone-tracker.html" style="color: var(--aether); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem;">
        Open Zone Tracker &rarr;
      </a>
    </p>

    <!-- ── Combat Tracker ────────────────────────────── -->

    <h2 id="combat-tracker">Combat Tracker</h2>

    <p>
      A visual timing track for combat. Add players and NPCs to the roster,
      drag their tokens to the count where their action resolves, and advance
      the timeline as the fight unfolds. The track extends infinitely &mdash;
      it always shows 30 counts ahead of the current position.
    </p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Feature</th><th>What It Does</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Roster</td><td>Add PCs and NPCs with names; auto-assigned color tokens</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drag &amp; drop</td><td>Drag tokens to any count on the timeline, or between counts</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Advance 1 Count</td><td>Step forward one count at a time</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Next Action</td><td>Skip ahead to the next count that has a token</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Infinite timeline</td><td>Track auto-extends as combat progresses; 30-count visible window</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Unplaced staging</td><td>Tokens waiting for placement sit in a staging area below the track</td></tr>
    </table>

    <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
      <a href="tools/combat-tracker.html" style="color: var(--galvanic); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem;">
        Open Combat Tracker &rarr;
      </a>
    </p>

